# Light profile: minimal compact blocks. Early mainnet (Zcash launched Oct 2016 at
# very low volume) is near coinbase-only — the floor of serialization work, a clean
# contrast to the shielded `dense` profile. Unlike a busy pre-Sapling range (which
# is transparent-tx-heavy and so serves *large* blocks on unfiltered GetBlock),
# early blocks are small on every request type and on disk. Validate the density
# line at extraction; drop BASE further if it is not ~1 tx/block.
# Consumed both as a Compose --env-file and sourced by the harness scripts, so
# keep it plain KEY=value with no quoting or `export`.
PROFILE=light
BASE=20000
SPAN=12000
RUST_CACHE_VOLUME=rust-cache-light
GO_CACHE_VOLUME=go-cache-light
